1. Tool Used
I used Canva to create the infographic.
Canva provides ready-made templates, icons, and easy drag-and-drop features.
It helped me design a clean and visually attractive infographic quickly.
2. What My Design Shows
My infographic explains what Digital Literacy is (ability to use digital tools safely and effectively).
It includes useful digital tools for students like Google Docs, email, and online platforms.
It also highlights safe internet practices such as strong passwords and avoiding scams.
3. Key Learning / Importance
Digital literacy is important for education, communication, and career growth.
It helps students stay safe online and avoid cyber threats.
It builds a professional online presence and improves digital skills.
4. Difficulty / Interesting Part
The most interesting part was selecting icons and arranging content creatively.
The difficult part was fitting all information into one page without making it crowded.
I learned how to balance text and visuals effectively.
